. 7. Solid understanding of product lifecycle and project management processes. 8. Strong business acumen and problem-solving skills. 9. Entrepreneurial and hands-on while being flexible and resourceful. 10. Ability to prioritize work and juggle multiple responsibilities effectively. OUR IDEAL CANDIDATE 1. Has a purpose-driven and a consistent history of delivering results with software solutions over the past 7 years. 2. Understands the problems that will be faced from early onboarding to hyper-growth and is excited to tackle these challenges head-on. 3. Has a clear vision of what a successful product, design, and engineering organization looks like and how to achieve it. 4. Makes an impact on the business and organization beyond his/her immediate team. 5. Strives for continuous improvement and development. Never settles and is continuously looking for the next challenge or next step to grow and expand. 6. Leads by example with top-notch communication skills and ensures the team understands and adheres to company standards and operating procedures. 7. Attracts, retains, develops, and inspires world-class talent. 8. Thrives under uncertainty and ambiguity. Persistent and motivated and motivating under pressure. 9. A professional that understands how to build scalable technology. 10. Passion for digital transformation. 11. Knowledge and experience of work in developing markets is a plus 12. Has a proven track record of leadership in areas of technology and product. Skills Experience in DLT technologies (Hyperledger suite of platforms is a plus) and C++, Java, Python, Ruby, Solidity, and Go. Compensation Salary (primarily equity-based) scales to market rates as business receives financing rounds , incentive share options Plan, and bonuses + Equity ", 
